\b\fs26 \cf0 Installation
\b0\fs22 \
You install ByteController as you install any other Mac OS X application. Simply move or copy ByteController.app to your "Applications" directory. You can also put it in the "Utilites" subdirectory.\
\
To make ByteController start up when you log in, either open ByteController's preferences (see 
\b Use
\b0 ) and select "Load at Startup". Or go to the Accounts pane of System Preferences, select your user, go to "Startup Items" and add ByteController to the list. Both methods are equivalent.\
\

\b\fs26 Use
\b0\fs22 \
To bring up the context menu, either click and hold the Play/Pause button or ctrl click anywhere on the controls.\
\
To apply skins, double-click the skin files. The appearance will change immediately. Skins can be managed in the Appearance tab in Preferences.\
